            review: "I have seen a lot of good reviews about this class and decided to give it try this summer. I have to say I'm a little disappointed and I really think it's overrated.\nThings I like:\n\nI really like the lecture videos, they are easy to follow and moreimportantly tightly related to the projects.\nIt's a good introduction to Python, Numpy, Pandas and Matplotlib if you are new to coding.\n\nThings I dislike:\n\nThe whole class is basically taught by TAs, I haven't seen Prof Joyner in any of the videos or weekly officer hours the whole semester, maybe there are some other classes like this too but it's different from all 4 courses I took before this one.\nAll the report parts in the projects are making grading very subjective, unlike the Computer Network course, in which they give you the exact questions to answer, this one is way more general, which makes it easy to miss things, you can get 100% when you thought you did bad but get only 50% when you thought you did ok. Some of the requirements ask you to include definitions for financial terms and formulas, you need to be careful and cite everything, otherwise, you might be taking a risk of committing plagiarism.\nThere's something due every week if you take it for the summer semester, if you don't figure out how much time each project takes you may get caught off guard and can't finish your assignment in time due to the unstable workload.\n",
